<chapter xml:id="ch-rootfinding" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Rootfinding</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
      Rootfinding is the process of finding values <m>p</m> such that <m>f(p)=0</m> for a function <m>f</m>. This is identical to solving equations <m>f(x)=g(x)</m>.  In this chapter, we learn techniques to estimate roots.
    </p>
  </introduction>
  <xi:include href="./sect-intro-rootfinding.ptx" />
  <xi:include href="./sect-bisection.ptx" />
  <xi:include href="./sect-fixed-point.ptx" />
  <xi:include href="./sect-newtons-method.ptx" />
</chapter>